sentences: Carlos López Estrada (born September 12, 1988) is a Mexican filmmaker, music video director, commercial director, theatre director and actor.
He made his feature film directorial debut in 2018 with Blindspotting.
The film premiered at the 2015 Palm Springs International Festival of Short Films.
López Estrada directed his first feature film in 2017, Blindspotting, starring  Daveed Diggs and Rafael Casal.
The film, released in 2018, is semi-autobiographical and based on Diggs and Casal's lives in a rapidly gentrifying Oakland.
López Estrada is also set to direct an original animated film at Disney, set for release in 2023.
In 2011, López Estrada directed a music video for Mexican pop band Jesse & Joy of their song "Me Voy."

The video, which uses stop motion and found the production team trimming 2900 photographs in order to create the sequences included, earned the title of Best Short Form Music Video at the 13th Annual Latin Grammy Awards in 2012.

In 2013, López Estrada co-directed a music video for Capital Cities’ "Kangaroo Court" which features American actor Darren Criss and American actress Shannon Woodward.
In 2015, López Estrada directed a video for Thundercat's "Them Changes", which featured artists Flying Lotus and Kamasi Washington.
In 2018, López Estrada directed the music video for Billie Eilish's "When the Party's Over".
In 2021, López Estrada directed the music video for Katy Perry's "Electric" song in collaboration with the Pokémon franchise for its 25th anniversary.
In 2018, López Estrada directed the second episode of the final season of Legion, titled "Chapter 21".
The episode was released in July 2019.
In October 2015, López Estrada starred in an original multimedia theatre show, titled Ded!.
As of October 2019, Walt Disney Animation Studios announced that they were developing a feature film with López Estrada.
